data.name: Test1
data.latex:
A rubber ball of mass \( \mathrm{m} \) and radius \( \mathrm{r} \) is submerged into water of density \( \rho \) to
the depth \( \mathrm{h} \) and released. Then to what height will the ball jump up above
the surface of water?
(A) \( \left(\rho \frac{4}{3} \pi r^{3}-m\right) \frac{h}{m} \)
(B) \( \left(\mathrm{m}-\rho \frac{4}{3} \pi \mathrm{r}^{3}\right) \frac{\mathrm{h}}{\mathrm{m}} \)
(C) \( \left(\rho \frac{4}{3} \pi r^{3}-m\right) \frac{h}{2 m} \)
(D) \( \left(\rho \frac{4}{3} \pi r^{3}+m\right) \frac{h}{m} \)
